<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8391> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8391" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, on Pompey." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8280> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8280" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText " Quaestor, more probably in 91 than 90 (Plut. Sert. 4.1), since Plutarch has him elected promptly after his return from Spain and also when the Marsic war was breaking out (#). He was assigned to Cisalpine Gaul, where he levied troops, procured arms, and continued active as a proquaestor (Plut. 4.1-2; cf. Sall. Hist. 1.88M). See Sumner, Orators 107-108; Spann, Sertorius 20-24. Rejected for the tribunate of the plebs of 88 or 87 through Sulla's opposition (Plut. Sert. 4.2; discussion in Spann, 24-30), preferably in 89 for 88, as his defeat appears to precede Sulla's march on Rome in 88 (Plut. loc. cit.; Spann, 24ff.; Ch. F. Konrad, Sertorius 7-12, 204, note 18). No ancient text mentions his praetorship, but the regular assignment of Hisp. Cit. to his command (App. BC 1.86, cf. 108; Ib. 101) at a time much #) earlier than his departure to Spain late in 83 strongly implies that he had held it. Schulten's date in 87 seems to be a slip (Sertorius 38), but Sertorius may  well have reached the legal age by 86, and have been praetor in 85 or 84, a date consistent with his activity in Italy (Spann, op. cit.). It seems better, rather than accept an intervening loss of imperium before he went to Spain, to assume that he kept his imperium as procos. (Spann, 37-51; Konrad, 15-26). He may have received command over both Spanish provinces as Annius Luscus did in 81 against him (MRR 2.77; see Badian, Studies 96, 104, note 164-165). Procos. in Spain. See MRR 2.90, and annually to 72 for sources. On his campaigns, see above, on Q. Caecilius Metellus Pius (98), and Cn. Pompeius Magnus (31). Spann places the siege of Contrebia (Liv. 91, fr. 22) in the autumn of 77. If his assassination has been correctly re-dated to 73, the notice regarding it in MRR 2.118 under 72 should be transferred to 73, MRR 2.112, with the addition of references to Strabo 3.4.10, 161C; Amm. Marc. 26.9.9, and with a special reference to App. Mith. 72. On the discovery that the site of Contrebia was at Botorrita, see A. Balil, Epigraphica 42, 1980, 199-202; and now J. S. Richardson, JRS 73, 1983, 33-41.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4509> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4509" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Murdered at Osca by a group of his subordinates (Sall. Hist. 3.84-87 M; Diod. 37.22a; Liv. Per. 96; Vell. 2.30.1; Plut. Sert. 25-28; Comp. Sert. et Eum. 2.3-4; Pomp. 20.2; App. BC 1.113-114; Ib. 101; Flor. 2.10.8-9; Iul. Exup. 8; Eutrop. 6.1.3; Oros. 5.23.13)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4431> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4431" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, Promagistrates, on Metellus and Pompey; below, Legates, on M. Perperna. Cf. App. BC 1.112." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4392> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4392" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, on Metellus and Pompey. Schulten (Sertorius 106f.) dates his alliance with Mithridates of Pontus by 75 at the latest (Cic. Verr. 2.1.87; Leg. Man. 9 and 46; Mur. 32; Sall. Hist. 2.79, and 93M; Liv. Per. 93; Plut. Sert. 23-24; App. Mith. 68, and 70, and 112; Oros. 6.2.12; Ps.-Ascon. 244 Stangl; Magie, Roman Rule in Asia Minor 1.322f.; 2.1203, note 1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4355> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4355" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, on Caecilius Metellus, and Pompey." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4324> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4324" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His power in Spain reached its height this year (Plut. Sert. 14-17). See above, on Metellus and Pompey; and Legates, on Perperna." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4297> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4297" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 80, Promagistrates, note 6; and above, on Caecilius Metellus and Manlius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4274> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4274" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 80, Promagistrates, and note 6; and above, on Caecilius Metellus Pius, Domitius Calvinus, and Hirtuleius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4250> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4250" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Returned to Spain at the request of the Lusitanians, and defeated Cotta at sea and Fufidius on land (Sall. Hist. 1.104-109M; Plut. Sert. 10.1-12.3; of. App. Ib. 101; see above, Promagistrates, on Cotta and Fufidius)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4249> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4249" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "6 Sertorius no longer had legal standing with the government in Rome, but continued to use the regular Roman titles for his government in Spain (Plut. Sert. 22.3-23.5; App. BC 1. 108; see 79, Quaestors, on Hirtuleius)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4215> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4215" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Expelled from Spain by the Proconsul C. Annius, he won support in Africa and in 80 returned at the invitation of the Lusitanians (Sall. Hist. 1.94-103M; Plut. Sert. 7.1-11.1; cf. Flor. 2.10.1-2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4165> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4165" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Retired to Spain where he found popularity and support (Sall. Hist. 1.94M; Plut. Sert. 6.3-5; see 83, Praetors)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4113> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4113" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "First assisted Scipio and Norbanus against Sulla, then retired to Etruria, and proceeded from there to his province of Nearer Spain (Plut. Sert. 6.1-3; App. BC 1.86; Ib. 101; cf. Iul. Exup. 7-8, still in Rome at the end of the year)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4046> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4046" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fled with Cinna and returned as one of his chief officers (Liv. Per. 79; Plut. Sert. 4.4-5.3; App. BC 1.65; Flor. 2.9.13; Gran. Lic. 23B; Oros. 5.19.9). His forces encountered those of Pompeius Strabo (Sisenna fr. 129 Peter; Liv. Per. 79; Val. Max. 5.5.4; Gran. Lic. 25B; Oros. 5.19.10-13), and shared in the battle on the Janiculum (Liv. Per. 80; cf. Gran. Lic. .25B). He opposed giving leadership to Marius, and the reign of terror (Plut. Sert. 5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3855> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3855" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served in Cisalpine Gaul, where he levied troops and procured arms for use in the Social War (Plut. Sest. 4.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3772> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3772" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Didius in Nearer Spain (see 97-94, Tribunes of the Soldiers)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3756> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3756" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Didius in Nearer Spain (see 97-93, Tribunes of the Soldiers)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3742> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3742" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Didius in Nearer Spain (see 97-93, Tribunes of the Soldiers)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3733> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3733" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 97-93, Tribunes of the Soldiers." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3715> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3715" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served with distinction under Didius in Nearer Spain, winning the corona graminea at Castulo (Sall. Hist. 1.88 M-Gell. 2.27.2; Plin. NH 22.12; Plut. Sert. 3.3; see 96-93, Tribunes of the Soldiers)." .
